iao_definition: ['a data item is an information content entity that is intended to be a truthful statement about something (modulo, e.g., measurement precision or other systematic errors) and is constructed/acquired by a method which reliably tends to produce (approximately) truthful statements.', 'An information content entity that is intended to be a truthful statement about something (modulo, e.g., measurement precision or other systematic errors) and is constructed/acquired by a method which reliably tends to produce (approximately) truthful statements.']
label: ['data item', 'data item']

iao_definition: ['Includes individuals who either self-report or have been described by authors as\n\nEuropean, Caucasian, White or one of the sub-populations from this region (e.g Dutch). This category also includes individuals who genetically cluster with reference populations from this region, for example 1000 Genomes and/or HapMap CEU, FIN, GBR, IBS and TSI populations.']
label: ['European']

iao_definition: ['A member of the class of isoxazoles that is 1,2-oxazole substituted by a 2-(methanesulfonyl)-4-(trifluoromethyl)benzoyl group and a cyclopropyl group at positions 4 and 5, respectively. It is a 4-hydroxyphenylpyruvate dioxygenase inhibitor which is used as a herbicide for weed control in maize and sugarcane.']
label: ['isoxaflutole']

iao_definition: ['A part of a document used to summarize the findings discussed in the document. The conclusion section is typically found near the end of a document.']
label: ['conclusion section']

iao_definition: ['A compound based on a five-membered heterocyclic aromatic skeleton containing one N and one O atom.', 'An azole based on a five-membered heterocyclic aromatic skeleton containing one N and one O atom.']
label: ['oxazole']

iao_definition: ['An identifier is an information content entity that is the outcome of a dubbing process and is used to refer to one instance of entity shared by a group of people to refer to that individual entity.']
label: ['identifier']

iao_definition: ['When two or more amino acids combine to form a peptide, the elements of water are removed, and what remains of each amino acid is called an amino-acid residue.']
label: ['amino-acid residue']

iao_definition: ["A quality of a single process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's occurrence."]
label: ['occurrence']

iao_definition: ['population category defined using ancestry informative markers (AIMs) based on genetic/genomic data']
label: ['ancestry category']

iao_definition: ['A compound used with herbicides that reduces the effect of the herbicide on crop plants or otherwise improves the selectivity of the herbicide for weed species over the crop plant.']
label: ['herbicide safener']
